{
  "texts": [
    "This has multiple positive implications for its adoption chances.",
    "First, PCI is free because the service is provided by volunteer recommenders and reviewers.",
    "Unlike a traditional journal, however, no publisher is benefiting from volunteer reviewers -the benefit is solely conferred to the preprint authors.",
    "Second, an open access model with no APCs can help battle publication bias.",
    "If a move away from accept/reject decisions can improve the cost/benefit of complete reporting, the zero cost might limit any additional discouragement of producing manuscripts."
  ]
}